caption: I don’t know where any of these people went that gave this place a good review.  The place and the furniture are run down. There menu online is not the one that we had to choose from which was written on a piece of paper and cut out with scissors.  All the food was cheap frozen food they dropped in a fryer. It was terrible bad bar food.  It’s served in styrofoam containers...like cheap bar food.  Extremely limited drink menu that they didn’t have some ingredients to make.  Ordered a Hurricane and it wasn’t even the right color and was awful.  Of all the great places to go in New Orleans to eat this is definitely not one of them.  Ordered our food and drinks, tasted them and then paid the bill and left. Not even worth fighting over.
Great atmosphere.  A little pricey

That: Roof-Top Bar & Grillé Vibe; close to 360 degree Views of The Beautiful City of New Orleans. Enjoy small bites, or tasty Burgers and of course a great assortment of mixed-drinks. Low couch seating or traditional table top, all within the warmth of the fire. Would recommend, both local and for, "out-of-town(ers)." Cheers!!
Amazing views of the city!!!
Fun place nice food and drinks

Had reservations was seated in the bar ordered a drink and food then waited an1 hour 20 min without anyone checking on us. Then gratuity was added on a part of two. No big deal since we weren't even able to order!! Terrible service

Absolutely beautiful view here. We stayed in the hotel and really enjoyed hopping up here for a drink. Drinks were good, food was pretty decent and everyone working was beyond friendly.  You can tell they are a little understaffed right now because service was always a little slow, but they were trying their hardest to get to everyone at quickly as possible.  Definitely would recommend coming up if you aren't in a hurry and just want to relax with a few drinks.

Ambiance and aesthetic are great but cocktails are a little lacking IMO. I love fruity cocktails,  but everything here was very heavy or spicy, so if that’s your thing it’s the place to be! Over all, nice but for a cocktail bar I’d like more variety
Beautiful city views and sunsets from the rooftop bar
Funky fun with some quirky cocktails that are delish!
The cocktails were great and the food was also good. The waitress was great but seemed stretched at times. Would definitely visit again.

The view is great, the food is good, the drinks are really tasty, but the service is slow, the severs are not attentive, and the experience felt like we were an inconvenience rather than guests. The servers marked us as “no show” on our reservation online, which affects our ability to make reservations in the future at places that use the Open Table app. But we were there. And they wouldn’t split the check which I know is an arbitrary decision made by either the staff serving us or the manager and it’s ridiculous. We should be able to split the Bill in half at least.  I’m pretty underwhelmed by the whole experience even though my friends and I made the best of it and wish the staff had made it feel more welcoming. If the management changes in the future, it has potential. The view and flavors were really nice so I would try them again one more time, but probably not make a reservation on a Tuesday and just come.

Not what I expected. The view and the place is nice, but the drinks and food were awful. Shrimp ceviche was more like a pico de gallo and had big chunks of onions and tomatoes. Too expensive for what it is. Do not recommend.
Very discourteous bartenders. I was polite and compliant with CDC guidelines and the behavior of the staff wad very much about lording authority over someone than concern for safety.
Took a while to get the one drink I ordered. Was over charged for it and the waitress added her own tip to my check. If it were not for the convenience I would not go back.
The worst drinks in the city. In 56 years of living I've never had a cocktail so bad
Hotel is nice. Avoid the bar , hostess rude and is messing up money for bartenders.

View was nice, the food was okay, however the waitress we had was downright rude. She rudely told us that she couldn't split the check, I offered to just cover the full tab and  was going to give her a full tip anyway (despite the level of service), she then didn't inform me that she had already added gratuity to the bill and we only had 3 people at the table!! Completely unacceptable in my honest opinion and I WORK in the service industry.
Excellent drinks and a great atmosphere.
Love the view. Pretty hipster but a nice crowd and servers. Good food! Bones and Frites (Roasted Bone Marrow served with French Fries) were delicious!

I have a bachelors degree in Hospitality Management and I have 10 plus years experience in the industry. I was really looking forward to the drinks here, but unfortunatly the service was lacking heavily. First off, they need a new manager and the staff needs retraining. When we asked the hostess about the Halloween festivities she was completely unaware of the sign posted outside about the costume contest. Second, when we asked about the Happy hour menu the server stated it was only for the drinks. She did not specify what drinks or anything else. When we got our check there was no happy hour price on any of our drinks. When we asked her about it, she said it was only for certain drinks. As a guest you are going to have to figure out the menu on your own I guess... Because of poor management it shows in the service.
Great view
Great views but the service was lacking. Maybe we just came on A bad day, but there's other beautiful rooftops we can visit next time.
Can't beat this view
Great low-key rooftop bar with a chill atmosphere, excellent cocktails, and a small scale, but ingenious, app selection.
Great view

Super cool atmosphere... accommodated us with great communication. Even brought us a big kitchen knife to cut the birthday cake they allowed us to bring in. Great service and all the food was really good too. I don’t post often for good experiences in Nola bc it’s kinda expected here... thanks monkey B for the great birthday experience.

I love how they’ve adjusted during the pandemic. Everyone’s socially distancing, the tables are all conveniently placed more than 6-feet apart. Menu can be found using a QR code and if you get there early enough, the food is amazing! I had the sliders with fries.  As always, the view is beautiful. A great day/night whenever you go.
The service was awful. It wasn't busy, our waitress was rude, and didn't check on us often. Spend your money elsewhere.
Absolutely amazing, chill, great drinks and social distancing practiced. A place to experience instead of just go.  Enjoy! Ill be baaaaack

At 7:30 we called only to talk to someone who seemed confused as to what was going on entirely. We were eventually seated around 7:45.

Went here for my staggette all the way from Vancouver, BC on Sat, May 25 and DJ wouldn't take a simple song request (BOASTY! Who wouldn't play that?!) Which was also surprising because everyone we encountered from NOLA would say all DJs play anything, especially requests! Anyways, he was SO RUDE about it and made the ONLY 11 ladies dancing, leave! Too bad because it was a nice spot and view but the DJ was a HUGE TURN OFF.
It's in my top 5 favorite places now. Food absolutely reasonable.  And absolutely amazing. Plus it's on a rooftop, so doesn't get any better!

The views are worth a visit to Monkey Board, especially at night. The lights are beautiful. The drinks are pricey, but very good. The staff were awesome, super friendly and very talkative. We visited this hotel based on a recommendation that they had a roof top where we could see the lunar eclipse. It was admittedly very cold night and the Saints had lost the NFC Championship earlier in the day. As recommended the view was incredible; however, the staff wanted to go home early and they made no bones about it. So I give them a 2-star for their honesty and for feeling the Saints pain; however, it felt weird being rushed out of a roof top location with many other patrons in New Orleans. With better weather and a Saints victory, I'm sure the experience would have been much different.

How long does it take 3 bartenders to serve 8 people. 20 minutes, how you may ask I timed it. After my drink took forever I timed multiple groups. 8 people should take no where near that amount of time.

Great view! Melanie was awesome. It was a little windy, but we toughed it out. Lots of power and comfy seating to lounge around. Awesome radio station! Nice restroom as well. Definitely worth going to even for a just couple bevies.

Cool vibe place. Def recommend this as a meet up spot with friends or get some alone time with a hot date 😀 even on a chilly night like tonight, they had heaters out, good tunes pumping and everybody was friendly. It’s inside the hotel, 17th floor.

Our  trip was during St. Patty's day/Spring Break March 15-18th.  We went on a friday night but before 7pm.  we walked our %ss from Canal to the hotel. The monkey board is at the very rooftop of a hotel.  Great vibe.  I felt spoiled bc we had our own DJ.  They were boiling crawfish, YUM.  So you could get 3 lbs of crawfish with fixins like pineapple. Hell yes it was so good.  The crawfish came with 2 coupons for a 16oz draft beer. ALL FOR $25!!!! The beer was whatever their house beer was for that night.  It was breezy up on the 17th floor, it was great view, great music.  I'd go back.  We had a great server.

Cool rooftop bar with comfy seating areas.  Beautiful views of the city. It was hard to get drinks as the bar was crowded.  Although it was only 9:40 they said the kitchen was closed.  We went to the first floor restaurant and they were closing, too.  We got lucky and the food and beverage manager let us sit and order.  When we told him what happened upstairs he comped our meal. We had a grench dip and a wedge salad.  The sandwich was very tasty with a generous amount of beef on a tasty crunchy roll and a little side of french onion soup. The wedge salad was also good.  Thanks for turning around a frustrating experience.

Easy to find with GPS. Parking across the street was $8 for 2hrs on a Saturday evening. Friendly and straight forward staff.  $11 for two specialty beers. $14 for pretzels with beer cheese & spicy asian wings. The wrap around seating areas offered plenty of options from picnic table to comfy couches. Go for the views & enjoy simple pub fare at a modest price for the location.
